%N A227989 Decimal expansion of Sum_{n >= 1} sigma_2(n)/n!.
%C A227989 Problem No. 45 from P. Erdős (see the 1963 link). The problem is "is Sum_{n = 1..oo} sigma_k(n)/n! an irrational number where sigma_k(n) is the sum of the k-th power of divisors of n?" This property has been proved with k = 1 and 2 (see the Breusch link for the proof).
